\section{Workflow Implementation}

The workflow will be implemented using Snakemake in order to provide reproducible, scalable, and portable execution.

The workflow will be controlled through:

\begin{itemize}
    \item a central configuration file,
    \item sample sheets,
    \item modular rule files including a Snakefile,
    \item Conda environments.
\end{itemize}

Existing Snakemake wrappers will be used whenever available. Wrappers improve reproducibility by providing standardized rule definitions and software environment specifications. For tools without available wrappers, Conda environments will be defined manually.

Exact software versions will be specified in Conda environment files in order to guarantee reproducibility across computational systems.

The workflow will be able to support execution on:

\begin{itemize}
    \item local workstations,
    \item Linux servers,
    \item HPC systems.
\end{itemize}

